House Bill 801 (AS PASSED HOUSE AND SENATE)
By: Representative DeLoach of the 167th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act to re-create and establish the Board of Commissioners of Long County,
2 approved March 10, 1988 (Ga. L. 1988, p. 3755), as amended, so as to revise the powers of
3 the chairperson of the board of commissioners; to provide for a county manager; to provide
4 an effective date; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
5 purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 An Act to re-create and establish the Board of Commissioners of Long County, approved
9 March 10, 1988 (Ga. L. 1988, p. 3755), as amended, is amended by revising Section 4 and
10 adding a new section to read as follows:
11 "SECTION 4.
12 Chairperson.
13 The chairperson of the board shall:
H. B. 801
- 1 -

25 LC 47 3633/AP
14 (1) Preside at all meetings of the board unless otherwise adopted by appropriate
15 resolution. The rules of order shall be governed by Robert's Rules of Order unless
16 otherwise adopted by appropriate resolution; and
17 (2) Be recognized as the official head of Long County, Georgia, by state, federal, and
18 other authorities.
19 SECTION 4.1.
20 County manager.
21 (a) The board shall employ a county manager who shall be responsible for the supervision,
22 direction, and control of the administration of the affairs of Long County. The board shall,
23 by appropriate ordinance, set and determine the terms and conditions of employment,
24 limitations of authority, scope of duties, compensation, and grounds for termination of the
25 county manager.
26 (b) In the event of a vacancy in the office of county manager, whether by reason of death,
27 incapacity, or termination, the board may, by majority vote upon a proper motion at a
28 meeting held pursuant to Code Section 50-14-1 of the O.C.G.A., authorize the chairperson
29 of the board to serve as interim county manager; provided, however, that such authorization
30 shall expire 90 days following such vote by the board."
31 SECTION 2.
32 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2025.
33 SECTION 3.
34 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
